You forgot the bubble gum and duct tape.  What respectable air machine would be without them. Also, those pop cans do a nice job on the bullet holes; just rivet them in place.<br><br>
By the way, I ain't lookin' at site 164 or some of those other sites nomore.  It's a waste of time, and that, in the long run, is all we have.  <br><br>
Many of us feel that this is a gift (our time right now) that many others, whom we honor tomorrow, did not receive. In this life we make many choices, and those reflect the type of person we have become, and will become.  I firmly believe that our choices of language, where we spend time, how we behave, and the stories we tell (and those we decide not to tell) determine who we really are, and what we are made of.  <br><br>
The &quot;old fashoned&quot; virtues of telling the truth, having determination, building character, taking a stand and basic honesty are apparently &quot;the counterculture&quot; now.  (If you don't believe me, see yesterday's Parade Magazine about a reporter observing a Marine boot camp.)  <br><br>
It's time we build the type of site we can be proud of having not only our kids, but our grandkids and their children, read. 
